Sentencas: A low-temperature proton conductor electrolyte with CO2 tolerance that had a smaller drop in performance with decreasing operation temperature was developed.
Titulo: A High Electrochemical Performance Proton Conductor Electrolyte with CO2 Tolerance

Sentencas: A Ni-anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) comprising a proton-conducting BaZr0.4Ce0.4Y0.2O3 (BZCY4) electrolyte and a Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3 (BSCF) perovskite cathode was fabricated.
Titulo: A High Electrochemical Performance Proton Conductor Electrolyte with CO2 Tolerance

Sentencas: An anode-supported thin-film electrolyte fuel cell was fabricated by the dual dry pressing/sintering process.
Titulo: A High Electrochemical Performance Proton Conductor Electrolyte with CO2 Tolerance

Sentencas: A peak power density of 219 mW/cm(2) was achieved at 750 degrees C while it still was 57 mW/cm(2) at 400 degrees C when operating on humidified H-2 fuel using a cell with a 32 mu m thick electrolyte.
Titulo: A High Electrochemical Performance Proton Conductor Electrolyte with CO2 Tolerance
